  "text": "Despite the criticisms directed at projective techniques by quantitatively-oriented researchers, there is evidence, although modest, suggesting projective techniques can demonstrate satisfactory levels of validity. This evidence consists of construct, predictive and concurrent validity, in addition to face, content and logical validation, which are essentially judgmental [CITATION_1] .",
